trans-unit.source: Represents the exception class for parser-specific exceptions from a WPF XAML parser.
trans-unit.target: Representerer unntaksklassen for parseren-spesifikke avvik fra en WPF XAML parser.

trans-unit.source: This exception is used in XAML API or WPF XAML parser operations from [!INCLUDE[net_v30_short](~/add/includes/net-v30-short-md.md)] and [!INCLUDE[net_v35_short](~/add/includes/net-v35-short-md.md)], or for specific use of the WPF XAML parser by calling <xref href="System.Windows.Markup.XamlReader"></xref> API.
trans-unit.target: Dette unntaket er brukt i XAML API eller WPF XAML parseren-operasjoner fra [!INCLUDE[net_v30_short](~/add/includes/net-v30-short-md.md)] og [!INCLUDE[net_v35_short](~/add/includes/net-v35-short-md.md)], eller for bestemte bruk av WPF XAML parseren ved å kalle <xref href="System.Windows.Markup.XamlReader"> </xref> API.

trans-unit.source: XamlParseException is used only for the WPF-implemented XAML parser that performs the XAML parsing and loading for WPF applications.
trans-unit.target: XamlParseException brukes bare for WPF implementert XAML parseren som utfører XAML analyse og laste inn for WPF programmer.

trans-unit.source: Specifically, the exception is only relevant when an application targets [!INCLUDE[net_v30_short](~/add/includes/net-v30-short-md.md)] and [!INCLUDE[net_v35_short](~/add/includes/net-v35-short-md.md)].
trans-unit.target: Nærmere bestemt unntaket gjelder bare når et program har [!INCLUDE[net_v30_short](~/add/includes/net-v30-short-md.md)] og [!INCLUDE[net_v35_short](~/add/includes/net-v35-short-md.md)].

trans-unit.source: The exception can also originate from user code in run-time calls to APIs that hook up the WPF-implemented XAML parser to load XAML from within a running WPF application (for example, calls to <xref:System.Windows.Markup.XamlReader.Load%2A?displayProperty=fullName>).
trans-unit.target: Unntaket kan også er hentet fra brukerkode i kjøretid kall til APIer koble WPF implementert XAML parseren ikke laste inn XAML fra i et program som kjører WPF (for eksempel kall til <xref:System.Windows.Markup.XamlReader.Load%2A?displayProperty=fullName>).</xref:System.Windows.Markup.XamlReader.Load%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: For [!INCLUDE[net_v40_short](~/add/includes/net-v40-short-md.md)], the <xref:System.Xaml.XamlParseException> exception that typically reports XAML processing exceptions is defined in a different namespace (<xref:System.Xaml>) and a different assembly (System.Xaml).
trans-unit.target: For [!INCLUDE[net_v40_short](~/add/includes/net-v40-short-md.md)], <xref:System.Xaml.XamlParseException>unntak som vanligvis rapporter XAML behandling unntak som er definert i et annet navneområde (<xref:System.Xaml>) og en annen samling (System.Xaml).</xref:System.Xaml> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlParseException>

trans-unit.source: Unless you are writing an equivalent to the WPF XAML parser or working with [!INCLUDE[net_v30_short](~/add/includes/net-v30-short-md.md)] and [!INCLUDE[net_v35_short](~/add/includes/net-v35-short-md.md)] targeting, you generally will not throw XamlParseException from your own code.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du skriver et tilsvarende til WPF XAML parseren eller arbeide med [!INCLUDE[net_v30_short](~/add/includes/net-v30-short-md.md)] og [!INCLUDE[net_v35_short](~/add/includes/net-v35-short-md.md)] målretting, du vanligvis kan ikke slette XamlParseException fra din egen kode.

trans-unit.source: However, handling for the exception is sometimes necessary.
trans-unit.target: Behandler for unntaket er noen ganger nødvendig.

trans-unit.source: For application scenarios, where you may want to suppress XAML parse errors, a <xref:System.Windows.Threading.Dispatcher> <xref:System.Windows.Threading.Dispatcher.UnhandledException> event handler at the application level is one way to handle a run-time XamlParseException.
trans-unit.target: Programmet scenarioer der vil undertrykke XAML spaltes feil, en <xref:System.Windows.Threading.Dispatcher> <xref:System.Windows.Threading.Dispatcher.UnhandledException>hendelsesbehandling på programnivå er én måte å behandle en kjøretid XamlParseException.</xref:System.Windows.Threading.Dispatcher.UnhandledException> </xref:System.Windows.Threading.Dispatcher>

trans-unit.source: Whether to suppress exceptions or let them surface to user code depends on how you design your application for purposes of loading XAML, and the trust level that you assign to the XAML your application loads.
trans-unit.target: Om du skal undertrykke unntak eller la det surface til brukerkode er avhengig av hvordan du utformer programmet for å laste inn XAML, og klareringsnivået du tilordne til XAML programmet lastes inn.

trans-unit.source: For more information, see [XAML Security Considerations](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md) or "XAML Security" section of [XAML Overview (WPF)](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil ha mer informasjon, se [XAML sikkerhetshensyn](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md) eller XAML sikkerhet-delen av [XAML oversikt over (WPF)](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).

trans-unit.source: For pages of an application, when the XamlParseException is thrown, it is usually in the context of the `InitializeComponent` call made by your page class, which is the entry point for the WPF application model's usage of the WPF XAML parser at the per-page level.
trans-unit.target: Sider med en applikasjon, når XamlParseException et, er det vanligvis i forbindelse med den `InitializeComponent` kallet fra den side-klassen som inngangspunktet for WPF programmet modellens bruken av WPF XAML parseren på per side-nivå.

trans-unit.source: Therefore another possible handling strategy is to place `try/catch` blocks in `InitializeComponent`.
trans-unit.target: En annen mulig behandler strategi er derfor ikke plassere `try/catch` blokkerer `InitializeComponent`.

trans-unit.source: However, this technique does not integrate well with templates, visual design surfaces and other generated sources that hook up `InitializeComponent`.
trans-unit.target: Denne metoden er ikke integrert med maler, visuell utforming overflater imidlertid og andre generert datakilder dette opp `InitializeComponent`.

trans-unit.source: Gets base URI information when the exception is thrown.
trans-unit.target: Henter basere URI informasjon når den unntak.

trans-unit.source: Base URI is potentially available because of parser context when the exception occurred.
trans-unit.target: URI er potensielt tilgjengelig på grunn av parseren konteksten da unntaket oppstod.

trans-unit.source: Knowing the base URI can be useful for debugging cases where a resource resolution error is the underlying cause.
trans-unit.target: Vel vitende om grunntallet kan URI være nyttig for feilsøking tilfeller der en ressurs oppløsning feil underliggende årsaken.

trans-unit.source: The parser context base URI.
trans-unit.target: Konteksten parseren basere URI.

trans-unit.source: Gets the data that is required to serialize the specified object by populating the specified <xref href="System.Runtime.Serialization.SerializationInfo"></xref> object.
trans-unit.target: Henter dataene som kreves for å serialisere det angitte objektet ved hjelp av den angitte <xref href="System.Runtime.Serialization.SerializationInfo"> </xref> objektet.

trans-unit.source: GetObjectData sets a <xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.SerializationInfo> object with all the exception object data targeted for serialization.
trans-unit.target: GetObjectData angir en <xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.SerializationInfo>objekt med alle objektet unntaksdataene mål for serialisering.</xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.SerializationInfo>

trans-unit.source: During deserialization, the exception is reconstituted from the <xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.SerializationInfo> transmitted over the stream.
trans-unit.target: Under deserialisering, reconstituted unntaket fra den <xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.SerializationInfo>overføres via dataflyten.</xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.SerializationInfo>

trans-unit.source: The serialization information object to add the serialization data to.
trans-unit.target: Serialisering informasjon objektet til å legge til serialiseringsdataene til.

trans-unit.source: The destination for this serialization.
trans-unit.target: Målet for denne serialisering.
